'''Padbury Mining''' is an Australian mining corporation. It is publicly listed on the [[Australian Securities Exchange]].

==Overview==
It has 2000&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> of [[Tenement (law)|tenements]] in the [[Mid West (Western Australia)|Mid West]] part of [[Western Australia]].<ref name="profile">[http://www.padburymining.com.au/Corporate/Company-Profile Official website: Company profile]</ref> It has explored [[Peak Hill, Western Australia]], where [[magnetite]] was found in 2011.<ref name="profile"/>

In April 2014, reached an agreement with businessman [[Roland Bleyer]] to fund a port and railway project in [[Oakajee, Western Australia]].<ref name="benbutler">Ben Butler, [http://www.smh.com.au/business/padbury-minings-64b-financier-raises-questions-20140425-379or.html Padbury Mining's $6.4b financier raises questions], ''[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]'', April 26, 2014</ref><ref name="burrell">Andrew Burrell, [http://www.theaustralian.com.au/business/mining-energy/padbury-mining-abandons-65bn-oakajee-port-and-rail-project/story-e6frg9df-1226901227485# Padbury Mining abandons $6.5bn Oakajee port and rail project], ''[[The Australian]]'', April 30, 2014</ref> However, due to disparaging press coverage of Bleyer's past business dealings, the project was put on hold.<ref name="nickevans">Nick Evans, 'Padbury deal dead in water', ''[[The West Australian]]'', May 1, 2014, p. 61</ref> Moreover, the company stopped trading on 11 April 2014 after failing to meet the demands from the ASX.<ref name="nickevans"/> Bleyer criticised this decision, adding the project would have "created jobs for the working man that needs to feed his family."<ref name="nickevans"/>

==Board of directors==
*William Han (Non Executive Director).<ref name="boardofdirectors">[http://www.padburymining.com.au/contacts Official website: Board and Management]</ref>

